headline: BNY Mellon (BK) Earnings Growth Surges 48.6%, Reinforcing Bullish Profitability Narrative
summary: Bank of New York Mellon (BK) delivered impressive earnings growth over the past year, with earnings expanding by 48.6%, far outpacing its 3.5% annual growth average over the last five years. Net profit margins have also strengthened to 24.8%, up from 18.1% previously. While annual earnings are forecast to rise by 6.67% and revenue by 3.6%, both are expected to lag the overall US market’s projections of 15.6% and 10%, respectively.
